INSTALLATION NOTES for FabBSD/MACHINE OSREV


What is FabBSD?
---------------

FabBSD is an open-source, 4.4BSD-like operating system designed for
numerical control of machinery and instrumentation. FabBSD can be used to
control various types of equipment:

	- Machine tools: CNC milling machines, lathes, routers, lasers
	- Process control: Power supplies, heaters, chillers, valves, relays
	- Measurement: Optical encoders, thickness gauges, tachometers,
	  thermocouples

Due to the real-time aspect of its kernel, FabBSD is designed for use on
systems dedicated to machine control. Hardware requirements are minimal.
For instance, in a typical computer-aided machining setup, FabBSD running
on a 133MHz 486-class processor will control a set of 350kHz motor drives
with ease, with or without software-based closed-loop control.

FabBSD OSREV integrates a subset of the standard BSD system commands and
utilities from OpenBSD. The distribution also includes Binutils, GCC, gdb,
OpenSSH and Sudo. FabBSD adds programming interfaces such as cnc(3), a set
of command-line utilities and the machctld(8) daemon.

Because FabBSD is from Canada, the export of Cryptography pieces (such
as OpenSSH and IPsec) to the world is not restricted.

(NOTE: FabBSD can not be re-exported from the US once it has entered
the US.  Because of this, take care NOT to get the distribution from
an FTP server in the US if you are outside of Canada and the US.)

A comprehensive list of the improvements brought by the OSREV release
is available on the web at http://www.FabBSD.org/OSrev.html.
